<TITLE> Shakib captains tri-nation squad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31 (bdnews24.com)  Shakib Al Hasan has been made skipper of a 15-member Bangladesh squad for the tri-nation series beginning in Dhaka on January 4. Ex-rebels Shariar Nafees and Aftab Ahmed, who had played in the Indian cricket league, have been included in the team that will face India and Sri Lanka, Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) on Thursday said while announcing the squad. Mashrafe Bin Mortaza did not get place in the 15-member final squad while pacer Shafiul Alam was selected for the team in place of pacer Sahadat Hossain. The squad - Shakib Al Hasan (captain), Tamim Iqbal, Mohammad Ashraful, Raqibul Hasan, Mahmudullah Riyad, Mushfiqur Rahim, Naeem Islam, Abdur Razzak, Rubel Hossain, Nazmul Hossain, Syed Rasel, Imrul Kayes, Shahriar Nafees, Aftab Ahmed and Shafiul Islam. bdn
